st about it so i can start outfitting guild members or any guilded alts with any peices they can use.<br>
<br>
Oh and dont be shy about asking for any bits you need cus i started smithing for this reason in the first place <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Details on Armours<br>
<br>
Ok lots to put up here so please bear with me, i really dont mean to spam, hehe.<br>
<br>
Imbued armour types are tunare followers only, but the enchanted types are almost as good, and much less expected fails on the non imbued type of Koada'Dal Mithril (Plate)<br>
<br>
Imbued/Enchanted Elven chainmail - (HIE, ELF, HEF)<br>
This is nice caster wearable arour with nice ac and relatively good stats for wis and int, usually +3 on both for most peices, all of these items are trivial to me and ore costs are low so i can happily hand out these free to any guild member who can use.<br>
<br>
Koada'Dal Mithril (Plate) - (HIE, ELF, HEF)<br>
Oddly froggies can wear some peices of this, wearable by WAR, CLR, PAL, BRD, various peices give dex, cha, wis, str and agi. Ore costs for this are quite a kick in the ribs (roughly 84pp per folded sheet, 1 - 3 needed for each peice not counting fails) so i reluctantly must ask for ore costs to be covered for me or ill be a very broke ondaris hehe. But please dont let it put you off putting up a request. I like this stuff cus its blue.<br>
<br>
Acrylia Chain Armor - wearable by WAR, CLR, PAL, RNG, SHD, BRD, ROG, SHM all Races, make this occasionally to increase my smithing skill and all items to make it are dropped so no worries about costs. Whindstones for temper are rare drop so probably wont be able to make this in large quantities all that quickly.<br>
<br>
for full details on armour stats go to<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/secrets/smithing_stats_highelf.htm">www.eqtraders.com/secrets...ighelf.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> for elven cultural and <br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/secrets/recipes_smithing_armor_stats.htm">www.eqtraders.com/secrets..._stats.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
for acrylia chain.<br>
<br>
Details on smithing supplies<br>
<br>
Swirling Mist - Dropped off mist elementals, best place ive found to farm this is najena, also rare drop in Steamfont and twilight sea.<br>
<br>
Morning dew - this is tough to get hold of, foraged in Gfay and Lfay also rare drop off brownies in Lfay, mithrill plate tends to use up allot of these.<br>
<br>
Essence of Moonlight - relatively common drop in mistmoore, i can farm this myself easily<br>
<br>
Mithrill ore - Store baught but needs to be enchanted by enchanter, spell is levl 49.<br>
<br>
Leather Padding - low quality wolf/bear/cat pelts and spiderling silk<br>
<br>
Any of these items anyone can get to me would be greatly appreciated but are by no means required.<br>
<br>
Please try and be specific with which peices you would like and in which order so i know what to make hehe.I will try my best to get the requested peices to you quickly but it can be time consumeing so please be patient.<br>
<br>
Dont let that slot with cloths on it bother you, put up a post with a request! I am glad to find a way in which i can really benefit the pack <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
-------Ondaris(52nd level cleric of tunare)-------<br>
